The agent developer has added the functions below to your `run_js` environment. **They are JavaScript globals available only inside `run_js` code** — they are NOT separate tools you can invoke via the tool-call protocol. Trying to call `{{ (index .Tools 0).Name }}` as a top-level tool will fail with `tool not found: {{ (index .Tools 0).Name }}`; the only top-level tool you have is `run_js`{{ if .Siblings }} (and `promptAgent` for sibling delegation){{ end }}.

Call them by name inside `run_js` with a single object argument matching the declared input type. Return values are native JavaScript objects matching the declared output type.

```javascript
